# W3-CODE-EDITOR
Code Editor
This is a simple web-based code editor built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. The editor provides a user-friendly interface for writing and editing code. It supports multiple programming languages including JavaScript, HTML, CSS, Python, and more.

Features
Syntax highlighting for multiple programming languages.
Auto-indentation and auto-completion of code.
Line numbering to keep track of code.
Drag and drop file upload to open files.
Ability to save and download code files.
Easy to use user interface.
Usage
To use this code editor, simply open the index.html file in your web browser. Once opened, you will see a user-friendly interface with a text area to write your code. The editor will automatically detect the language you are using and provide syntax highlighting accordingly.

You can open existing files by dragging and dropping them into the editor. To save a file, click on the "Save" button and give your file a name. To download a file, click on the "Download" button and save the file to your computer.

